The paper discusses the theoretical analysis of stochastic search algorithms, which are commonly used in optimization problems. This topic falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Among these, cs.NE and cs.AI are the most likely categories as they specifically deal with optimization and search algorithms. However, cs.DS, cs.LG, and cs.SY are also relevant as they cover topics related to algorithms, optimization, and control systems.
